Memeory Layout
- Stack
- Heap
- Initialized data
- Uninialized data
- Text

Stack
- Store local variable
- Auto allocation and deallocation

Heap
- Dynamic memory allocation (explicit)
- 'new' keyword
- manually deallocation ('delete')

Text
- store excuting code 

Initialized Data 
- global/static

Uninitialized Data 
- declared but explicit initialization global/static

Reference:
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/memory-layout-of-c-program/
https://courses.engr.illinois.edu/cs225/sp2021/resources/stack-heap/
